The Angusu clan of Wanga sub-tribe of the Abaluhya still bury their elders while seated: This is the burial of Mzee Raphael Ichechi Musebe who died aged 102 years. Note the shape of the coffin allows a sitting position.[Benjamin Sakwa, Standard]  By George Orido | 1 month ago By Stevens Muendo | 3 months ago By Ndungu Gachane | 11 months ago By Caroline Chebet | 1 year ago